topic: Book Workflow Series ("Nobel laureates explorative search")

goals.1: Identify the BGP for obtaining the nobel laureates and the nominees with their relevant attributes
goals.2: Get the number of Italian, French and Iranian winners and check which nation won more awards in the last twenty years.
goals.3: Determine how many Literature nobel laureates have the following contries: Italy, Germany, France, Romania, Denmark, Iran, and China
goals.4: How many Literature Nobel award winners have a PhD (aka Doctorate of Philosophy) (you may check if they have a doctoral advisor)?
goals.5: Are there books from Litarature Nobel Award winners which are not present in the Vatican Library? (if so, who is the author with more books not in the Vatical Library)?

name: 82b80661c4

search_workflow.narrative: let's see for a nobel in literature if we have properties connecting it to authors
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?nobel wdt:P31 wd:Q37922 ; ?property ?object . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name }} limit 100

search_workflow.narrative: then let's start from authors and let's try and see if there is a connection to nobels
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P27 wd:Q38 ; wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; ?property wd:Q37922 . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's retrieve some literature nobel prize winners/nominees
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?author ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P1411 | wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 }} limit 50

search_workflow.narrative: let's look for interesting attributes
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P1411 | wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; ?property ?object . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }} limit 100
output: Internet Speculative Fiction Database author ID
Oxford Dictionary of National Biography ID
British Museum person or institution ID
Les Archives du Spectacle Person ID
Vegetti Catalog of Fantastic Literature NILF ID
Union List of Artist Names ID

search_workflow.narrative:
date of birth/place of birth, gender, spouses are properties that every person usually has. let's look instead into detention and lifestyle
let's also look for doctorates
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P1411 | wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; ?property ?object . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex(?name, '.*(doctor|detent|carcer|style).*', 'i') }} limit 100

search_workflow.narrative:
we find nothing more
let's see some authors that were incarcerated and where
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?name ?placeName where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P1411 | wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P2632 ?place . ?place <http://schema.org/name> ?placeName }} limit 25

search_workflow.narrative: let's see the lifestyles instead
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?name ?styleName where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P1411 | wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P1576 ?style . ?style <http://schema.org/name> ?styleName }} limit 25

search_workflow.narrative:
not much information to be found there
what about genre?
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?name ?genreName where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P1411 | wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; wdt:P136 ?genre . ?genre <http://schema.org/name> ?genreName }} limit 25

search_workflow.narrative: let's count the number of genres across nobel winners authors
search_workflow.query: select ?genre ?genreName (count(?author) as ?howmany) where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; wdt:P136 ?genre . ?genre <http://schema.org/name> ?genreName }} group by ?genre ?genreName order by desc(?howmany)

search_workflow.narrative:
since we didn't get very interesting information when looking for lifestyles, place of detention and so on
let's go back and find more general properties
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P1411 | wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; ?property ?object . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex (?name, '.*(age|spouse|children|sibling|brother|sister|birth|death|gender|husband|wife).*') }} limit 100
output: National Historical Museums of Sweden agent ID

search_workflow.narrative: let's count the number of spuses each nobel prize winner had
search_workflow.query: select ?author ?authorName (count(?spouse) as ?nSpouses) where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; wdt:P26 ?spouse . }} group by ?author ?authorName order by desc(?nSpouses) limit 100

search_workflow.narrative: that can't be right, let's use distinct
search_workflow.query: select ?author ?authorName (count(distinct ?spouse) as ?nSpouses) where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; wdt:P26 ?spouse . }} group by ?author ?authorName order by desc(?nSpouses) limit 100

select ?author ?authorName (count(?author) as ?nSpouses) where{{ {{ select distinct ?author ?spouse where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; wdt:P26 ?spouse . }} }} ?author <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName . }} group by ?author ?authorName order by desc(?nSpouses) limit 100

search_workflow.narrative: let's see them ordered by longevity
search_workflow.query: select ?author ?authorName ?age where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; wdt:P569 ?birthDate ; wdt:P570 ?deathDate . bind (year(?deathDate) - year(?birthDate) as ?age) . }} group by ?author ?authorName order by desc(?age) limit 100

search_workflow.narrative:
that formula doesn't consider months or days, google says bertrand russel died at 97, not 98
that's still a calculation i would do on the front end if need be, especially since there doesn't seem to be an age() function
search_workflow.query: select ?mannerOfDeath ?name (count(distinct ?author) as ?howmany) where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; wdt:P1196 ?mannerOfDeath . ?mannerOfDeath <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }} group by ?mannerOfDeath ?name order by desc(?howmany) limit 100

search_workflow.narrative:
2. Get the number of Italian, French and Iranian winners and check which nation won more awards in the last twenty years.
first of all let's get the nodes for Italy, France, Iran
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?country ?countryName where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; wdt:P17 ?country . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName . filter regex(?countryName, '.*(italy|iran|france).*', 'i') }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's see if there is another property for country
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; ?property ?object . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex(?name, 'country', 'i') }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's see the country of each author
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?author ?authorName ?country ?countryName where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName ; wdt:P27 ?country . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName }} order by asc(?countryName) limit 100

search_workflow.narrative: let's try again
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?country ?countryName where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922; wdt:P27 ?country . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName . filter regex(?countryName, '.*(italy|iran|france).*', 'i') . }} order by asc(?countryName) limit 100

search_workflow.narrative:
no iran...
let's just see the winners for italy, france, iran
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?author ?authorName ?countryName where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName ; wdt:P27 ?country . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName . filter regex(?countryName, '(italy|iran|france)', 'i') }} order by asc(?countryName)

search_workflow.narrative: to retrieve the date the award was received i need more prefixes though...
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; p:P166 ?awardedProperty . ?awardedProperty ?property ?value . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's try with the url
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/P166> ?awardedProperty . ?awardedProperty ?property ?value . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's remove awarded
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/P166> ?awardedProperty . ?awardedProperty ?property ?value . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's try and remove the name
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; <http://www.wikidata.org/prop/P166> ?awardedProperty . ?awardedProperty ?property ?value . }}

search_workflow.narrative:
the only thing i can think of is that there may be an entry of the type "Nobel prize XXXX" where XXXX is the year
i know that formula 1 seasons are stored like that
let's look at awards received by writers, doing a regex on the name of the award, checking if some have a year in the name
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?award ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 ?prize . ?prize <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex(?name, '.*(nobel).*', 'i') }} limit 100
output: Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine
Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel
list of Nobel laureates in Physiology or Medicine

search_workflow.narrative: the (incomplete) answer to point 2 is then
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?author ?authorName ?countryName where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName ; wdt:P27 ?country . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName . filter regex(?countryName, '(italy|iran|france)', 'i') }} order by asc(?countryName)

search_workflow.narrative: 3. Determine how many Literature nobel laureates have the following contries: Italy, Germany, France, Romania, Denmark, Iran, and China
search_workflow.query: select ?country ?countryName (count(distinct ?author) as ?howmany) where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; wdt:P27 ?country . ?country <http://schema.org/name> ?countryName . filter regex(?countryName, '(italy|iran|france|germany|romania|denmark|iran|china)', 'i') }} group by ?country ?countryName order by desc(?howmany)

select distinct ?author ?authorName where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName ; wdt:P184 ?advisor . }} limit 100

search_workflow.narrative: is there a relationship related to instruction?

search_workflow.narrative: now we have to figure out the property connecting a book to the vatican library

search_workflow.narrative: instead let's look at the properties for books
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; wdt:P800 ?book . ?book ?property ?object . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . ?object <http://schema.org/name> ?objectName . }} limit 100

search_workflow.narrative:
no property seems to indicate an archive
is it possible that the inverse is true? that it's the vatican archive to hold a certain book?
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; wdt:P800 ?book . ?vatican ?property ?book . ?vatican <http://schema.org/name> ?vaticanName . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex (?vaticanName, '.*vatican.*', ',') . }} limit 100

search_workflow.narrative: maybe the archive is on the authors themselves?
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; ?property ?vatican . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . ?vatican <http://schema.org/name> ?vaticanName . filter regex(?vaticanName, '.*vatican.*', 'i') . }}

search_workflow.narrative:
let's try and find the vatican library by a roundabout way, first by finding the vatican country, then by finding everything related to that country
first we have to find the class for a country, let's use italy
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?class ?name where{{ wd:Q38 wdt:P31 ?class . ?class <http://schema.org/name> ?name }}
select distinct ?country ?name where{{ ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex(?name, '.*vatican.*', 'i') }}
select distinct ?country ?name where{{ ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex(?name, 'vatican city', 'i') }}
select distinct ?country ?name where{{ ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q6256 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex(?name, '.*del vaticano', 'i') }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's try with sovereign state
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?country ?name where{{ ?country wdt:P31 wd:Q3624078 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex(?name, '.*vatican.*', 'i') }}

search_workflow.narrative: now let's try and see everything with "library" or "archive" that connects with the vatican city via the "country" property
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?subject ?name where{{ ?subject wdt:P17 wd:Q237 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex(?name, '.*(library|archive|libr|arch).*', 'i') }}
output: Archpriest of the Basilica di San Pietro in Vaticano
Scuola vaticana di paleografia, diplomatica e archivistica
list of archives in Vatican City
Archive of the Congregation for the Doctrine of the Faith

search_workflow.narrative:
we found the Vatican Library entity
let's attempt to connect works of nobel laureates in literature with the vatican library
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; wdt:P800 ?book . ?book ?property wd:Q213678 . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's try with 2 jumps
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property1 ?property2 ?name1 ?name2 where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; wdt:P800 ?book . ?book ?property1 ?middle . ?middle ?property2 wd:Q213678 . ?property1 <http://schema.org/name> ?name1 . ?property2 <http://schema.org/name> ?name2 . }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's attempt and connect nobel laureates to the vatican library directly
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property1 ?name1 where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 . ?author ?property1 wd:Q213678 . ?property1 <http://schema.org/name> ?name1 . }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's attempt and connect nobel laureates to the vatican library directly

search_workflow.narrative: maybe this is the wrong approach. is there a property for a book, related to vatican library, not pointing to it?
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; wdt:P800 ?book . ?book ?property ?value . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex(?name, '.*vatican.*', 'i') . }}

search_workflow.narrative:
this idea didn't seem bad. there are many IDs related to different collections, but not a single property for a vatican library id
let's try and see if the laureates instead have some property like that
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; ?property ?value . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?name . filter regex(?name, '.*vatican.*', 'i') }}

search_workflow.narrative: we have some authors with a vatican library id.
search_workflow.query: select ?author ?name (count(?book) as ?n) where{{ ?author wdt:P800 ?book ; <http://schema.org/name> ?name . {{ select distinct ?author where {{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 . filter not exists {{ ?author wdt:P1017 | wdt:P8034 ?id }} }} }} }} group by ?author ?name order by desc(?n) limit 10

search_workflow.narrative: coming back to the properties exiting a book, there is a "collection" property which has my interest
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?collection ?name where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; wdt:P800 ?book . ?book wdt:P195 ?collection . ?collection <http://schema.org/name> ?name . }}

search_workflow.narrative: let's attempt the inverse, connect the vatican library to a book
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?property1 ?name1 where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; wdt:P800 ?book . wd:Q213678 ?property1 ?book . ?property1 <http://schema.org/name> ?name1 . }}

select distinct ?property1 ?name1 ?property2 ?name2 where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; wdt:P800 ?book . wd:Q213678 ?property1 ?middle . ?middle ?property2 ?book . ?property1 <http://schema.org/name> ?name1 . ?property2 <http://schema.org/name> ?name2 . }}

select distinct ?property1 ?name1 ?property2 ?name2 ?property3 ?name3 where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; wdt:P800 ?book . wd:Q213678 ?property1 ?middle1 . ?middle1 ?property2 ?middle2 . ?middle2 ?property3 ?book . ?property1 <http://schema.org/name> ?name1 . ?property2 <http://schema.org/name> ?name2 . ?property3 <http://schema.org/name> ?name3 . }}

search_workflow.narrative:
i googled to find famous books stored in the vatican library, one of them is Codex Vaticanus
let's try and find its entity, if it exists
since we don't know the class for a book yet, nor we know if Codex Vaticanus has that class, we filter regex by its name, also connecting it already to the vatican library
we then look for the property that connects it to the vatican library
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?book ?name ?property ?propertyName where{{ ?book <http://schema.org/name> ?name ; ?property wd:Q213678 . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?propertyName . filter regex(?name, '.*codex.*vaticanus.*', 'i') . }}

search_workflow.narrative:
now we are sure that either collection or location connect a book to the vatican library
let's go back to the books of nobel laureates and see if they are located in the vatican library
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?author ?authorName ?book ?bookName where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName ; wdt:P800 ?book . ?book wdt:P195 | wdt:P276 wd:Q213678; <http://schema.org/name> ?bookName }} limit 20

search_workflow.narrative: just to make sure, let's see if there are authors, not nobel laureates, with books stored in the vatican library

select distinct ?property ?propertyName ?book ?bookName where{{ ?author wdt:P106/wdt:P279* wd:Q36180 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName ; wdt:P800 ?book . ?book ?property wd:Q213678; <http://schema.org/name> ?bookName . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?propertyName }} limit 20

search_workflow.narrative:
last stand, see if the author of a book stored in the vatican library brings us back to a nobel laureate
found above in the long list of properties exiting a book
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?authorName ?book ?bookName where{{ ?book wdt:P195|wdt:P276 wd:Q213678 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?bookName ; wdt:P50 ?author . ?author wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName . }} limit 50

search_workflow.narrative: let's remove as many constraints as possible
search_workflow.query: select distinct ?authorName ?book ?bookName ?property ?propertyName where{{ ?book ?property wd:Q213678 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?bookName ; wdt:P50 ?author . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?propertyName . ?author wdt:P166 wd:Q37922 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName . }} limit 50

select distinct ?authorName ?book ?bookName ?property ?propertyName where{{ ?book ?property wd:Q213678 ; <http://schema.org/name> ?bookName ; wdt:P50 ?author . ?property <http://schema.org/name> ?propertyName . ?author <http://schema.org/name> ?authorName . }} limit 50
